---
/**
 * distributed-systems/fundamentals · Figure 7 — "saga + compensations" (Level 10).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). References the shared #arw and #arwA arrowhead
 * markers rendered once by <Defs />. Lives as an .astro component because inline
 * SVG with kebab-case attrs is unreliable in MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A saga: forward local transactions, and on failure run compensating transactions in reverse"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">SAGA — no cross-service rollback; compensate in reverse</text
            >
            <g font-size="9.5">
                <rect x="20" y="34" width="150" height="34" rx="7" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect><text x="95" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#244a2e">reserve seat ✓</text
                >
                <rect x="200" y="34" width="150" height="34" rx="7" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect><text x="275" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#244a2e">charge card ✓</text
                >
                <rect x="380" y="34" width="160" height="34" rx="7" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect><text x="460" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7a2218"
                    >reserve hotel ✗</text
                >
                <line x1="170" y1="51" x2="198" y2="51" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
                ></line>
                <line x1="350" y1="51" x2="378" y2="51" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
                ></line>
                <rect x="20" y="100" width="150" height="34" rx="7" fill="#fff" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="95" y="121" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7a1f12">release seat</text>
                <rect x="200" y="100" width="150" height="34" rx="7" fill="#fff" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="275" y="121" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7a1f12">refund card</text>
                <line
                    x1="275"
                    y1="100"
                    x2="275"
                    y2="70"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-dasharray="3 3"
                    marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
                <line
                    x1="95"
                    y1="100"
                    x2="95"
                    y2="70"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-dasharray="3 3"
                    marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
                <line x1="198" y1="117" x2="172" y2="117" stroke="#7a1f12" marker-end="url(#arwA)"
                ></line>
            </g>
            <text x="280" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >compensating transactions semantically undo committed steps</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A saga models a cross-service operation as local transactions, each with a compensating
        transaction; on failure it walks back in reverse. It gives up <em>isolation</em> — the charge
        is briefly visible. (Garcia-Molina &amp; Salem, 1987.)
    </figcaption>
</figure>
